  "id": "019cf625-7dd3-7a72-90bd-3bd3299a912c",
  "content": "### Task 2.7: Refactor `GraphView` to split-panel layout with entry-level interaction\n\n        availableOrigins={[...new Set(data?.nodes.map(n => n.source_origin).filter(Boolean) as string[])]}\n      />\n      <canvas ref={canvasRef} ... />\n    </div>\n    {selectedEntryId && (\n      <div class=\"reader-panel\">\n        <DocumentReader\n          entryId={selectedEntryId}\n          onNavigate={(id) => {\n            setSelectedEntryId(id);\n            // Re-center: find the node's position in the simulation, update\n            // the canvas transform to center on it. Uses the existing\n            // offsetRef/scaleRef pattern already in GraphView:\n            // const node = nodesRef.current.find(n => n.id === id);\n            // if (node) { offsetRef.current = { x: -node.x + width/2, y: -node.y + height/2 }; }\n          }}\n          onClose={() => setSelectedEntryId(null)}\n        />\n      </div>\n    )}\n  </div>\n);\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add entry-level node rendering**\n\nAdd a `viewMode` state (`\"cluster\" | \"entry\"`) and a `focusCluster` state to track which cluster was clicked.\n\nWhen a cluster is clicked, switch to `\"entry\"` mode: reinitialize the D3 force simulation with the individual `GraphNode`s from that cluster. To return to cluster view, add a \"Back to clusters\" button.\n\n**Node color mapping** (from spec, by `content_role`):\n```typescript\nconst ROLE_NODE_COLORS: Record<string, string> = {\n  design: \"#7dd3fc\",\n  code: \"#5eead4\",\n  plan: \"#ffb07c\",\n  memory: \"#c4b5fd\",\n  finding: \"#ff8a80\",\n  decision: \"#f0c94c\",\n  instruction: \"#fcd34d\",\n  learning: \"#6ee7b7\",\n};\n```\n\n**Node shape mapping** (from spec, by `source_origin`):",
